        "# NASA CMAPSS Predictive Maintenance - Beginner Friendly\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 1: Import Libraries\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 2: Load Data\n",
        "column_names = ['unit_number', 'time_in_cycles'] + \\\n",
        "    [f'operational_setting_{i}' for i in range(1, 4)] + \\\n",
        "    [f'sensor_measurement_{i}' for i in range(1, 22)]\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('train_FD001.txt', sep=' ', header=None)\n",
        "df.dropna(axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
        "df.columns = +column_names\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 3: Basic EDA\n",
        "print(df.head())\n",
        "print(df.describe())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize sensor data for a sample engine\n",
        "engine_id = 1\n",
        "engine_df = df[df['unit_number'] == engine_id]\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
        "plt.plot(engine_df['time_in_cycles'], engine_df['sensor_measurement_2'])\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Cycle')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Sensor 2 Reading')\n",
        "plt.title('Sensor 2 over Cycles for Engine 1')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 4: Compute RUL\n",
        "rul_df = pd.DataFrame(df.groupby('unit_number')['time_in_cycles'].max()).reset_index()\n",
        "rul_df.columns = ['unit_number', 'max_cycle']\n",
        "\n",
        "df = df.merge(rul_df, on='unit_number', how='left')\n",
        "df['RUL'] = df['max_cycle'] - df['time_in_cycles']\n",
        "df.drop('max_cycle', axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 5: Feature Selection\n",
        "feature_cols = [col for col in df.columns if 'sensor_measurement' in col]\n",
        "X = df[feature_cols]\n",
        "y = df['RUL']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 6: Standardize Features\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 7: Train-Test Split\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X_scaled, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 8: Train Random Forest Regressor\n",
        "model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
        "model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 9: Evaluation\n",
        "y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f'RMSE: {rmse:.2f}')\n",
        "print(f'R² Score: {r2:.2f}')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 10: Plot Predicted vs Actual RUL\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
        "plt.scatter(y_test, y_pred, alpha=0.5)\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Actual RUL')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Predicted RUL')\n",
        "plt.title('Predicted vs Actual RUL')\n",
        "plt.plot([y_test.min(), y_test.max()], [y_test.min(), y_test.max()], 'r--')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
